{
  "text": "Vanda Mimi Palmer (VMP), a commercially viable orchid derived from the crossing of Vanda Tan Chay Yan and Vanda tessellata (Roxb.) Hk.f. ex G. Don, is endowed with the terrate-shaped flower of Vanda Tan Chay Yan as well as the tri-colour and strong floral scent of Vanda tessellata. Its sweet fragrance-producing ability earned it the Champion Award for Fragrant Orchid organized by produced a fragrance composed of terpenoid, benzenoid and phenylpropanoid compounds [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
